**Abstract:**
Extensive working notes dated July 20, 1993, titled "Varia," containing reflections on multiple topics central to the Chantilly project. Includes analysis of Frei's thesis on the eclipse of biblical narrative, discussion of Chenu's thesis about Aquinas and the scientific character of theology, a developed analysis of speech acts and performative language, reflections on second-order discourse and theoretical versus practical understanding, and extended engagement with Rorty on the mirror of nature. The document explores how philosophers mistakenly took theoretical knowledge as paradigmatic, privileging contemplation over practical engagement.

**AI Recommendation:** Rich collection of working notes integrating multiple themes of the Chantilly project; shows how Frei, Chenu, speech-act theory, and the practical-theoretical distinction connect.

